               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18020918-52-person407">
                  RICHARD 
                  DAVIS
               <interp inst="t18020918-52-person407" type="surname" value="DAVIS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18020918-52-person407" type="given" value="RICHARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18020918-52-person407" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             sworn. - I am clerk to Mr. Bolt. the <rs id="t18020918-52-viclabel277" type="occupation">wharfinger</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18020918-52-victim406 t18020918-52-viclabel277"></join>: On Friday the 13the of August, Between two and three o'clock, I saw the prisoner take a knife out of his pocket, and cut the bag of cotton which lay on the wharf, and take some out; I run and took him back to the wharf, with the cotton in an apron; I have often seen him before.<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="180209180026"></xptr>(Thomas Hunter, a constable, produced the cotton.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's defence. I asked Davis if he saw me cut the bag, and he said, no, before the Magistrate. <rs id="t18020918-52-verdict278" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18020918-52-verdict278" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>, aged 21.</p>
